{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nExisting installs need an explicit, discoverable heal trigger that respects the git-fsck\n(read-only) vs git-maintenance (mutating) convention, and the server boot path should\nconverge. Plain fsck stays read-only; healing is opt-in until the doctor epic lands.\n\n## What\nAdd `--fix` to `rebar fsck`. NOTE: today `rebar fsck` exposes ONLY `[--output json]` — there\nis no existing `--repair`/`--fix` (verified: tests/golden/cli_help/fsck__help.out and\nsrc/rebar/_cli/help/fsck.txt), so `--fix` is a clean ADDITIVE flag (no collision/rename).\nDefault `fsck` stays read-only and REPORTS an `ensures: N/M applied` line (honors `no_mutate`;\n`no_mutate` is the existing read-only mode used by library surfaces — plain CLI `fsck` is\nalready read-only, and `--fix` is the ONLY thing that enables mutation). `fsck --fix` runs\n`run_ensures()` (WS1) under the write lock and heals. Wire MCP server startup\n(`mcp_server.main`, after the --help check) to run `run_ensures()`. Update the fsck help\ngolden(s) and the fsck byte-parity tests (WS3 OWNS these — WS5 does not) for the new flag +\nreport line.\n\n## Scope\nIn: `--fix` flag + `ensures: N/M` report line + no_mutate gating, server-startup wiring, fsck\nhelp-golden + byte-parity test updates. Out: the registry/`run_ensures` (WS1), the write-path\nhint (WS2), behavioral non-fsck tests (WS5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `rebar fsck` (no flag) mutates nothing and prints an `ensures: N/M applied` line; library `no_mutate=True` surfaces stay read-only; `--fix` is the only mutation-enabling flag\n- [ ] `rebar fsck --fix` runs `run_ensures()` and is git-level idempotent: two `--fix` runs on a converged store produce zero new commits/pushes\n- [ ] MCP server startup runs `run_ensures()` after the --help check (a booted server is converged)\n- [ ] fsck help golden(s) updated for `--fix`; fsck byte-parity tests updated and owned by WS3; a converged store's plain-fsck output changes only by the new report line"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783571783998171001,"uuid":"92b1ab2c-1b41-4cd5-8185-d5f17b76c8b0"}